# /voice-clone — Family L — Speech & Voice AI

You are running the `/voice-clone` skill. This designs and stages a voice-cloning
pipeline. The skill picks the right cloning tier (zero-shot / few-shot / full),
generates a data + training + watermark + eval plan, and produces a signed
CONSENT.md the user MUST review before any data is collected.

**The consent declaration is non-negotiable.** This skill REFUSES to write any
clone-config or initiate any data-prep step until CONSENT.md is signed by the
voice owner OR a licensed-actor agreement is on file. There is no `--skip-consent`
flag. There is no `--research-only` bypass. This is a hard floor.

This skill does NOT clone the voice itself — that's `/finetune --domain speech-tts`
downstream. This skill produces the build plan + the consent + the watermarking
keys + the attribution test.

---

## When to use

- Hall (or any voice owner) wants a synthetic clone of their own voice.
- A licensed voice actor is producing a synthetic persona under contract.
- A character voice (synthetic from scratch, no real person) needs the same
  watermark + attribution infrastructure as a real-person clone.

Do NOT use for:
- "Clone any voice from a YouTube clip" — refuse. This skill requires consent.
- Multi-voice TTS where each voice is real and unconsented — refuse. Route the
  user to `/tts-design` and have them line up consent per voice first.
- TTS for fictional / public-domain characters — that's `/tts-design` with a
  cleaner architecture call.

---

## Inputs

| Input | Required? | Format |
|---|---|---|
| Voice owner identity | yes | Name + role (self / licensed actor / synthetic persona) |
| Consent declaration | yes | Signed CONSENT.md (skill generates the template; user signs) |
| Voice samples | yes | Path to audio directory (per-tier minimums below) |
| Target quality tier | yes | "demo" / "production" / "studio" |
| Deployment use case | yes | "own voice (Hall speaks)" / "licensed actor (agent voice)" / "synthetic persona (no real person)" |
| Languages | yes | BCP-47 list (single or multi) |
| Expression scope | optional | "neutral" / "emotion-tagged" / "free-form" (drives backbone choice) |
| Existing TTS architecture | optional | If `/tts-design` already ran, point at the slug |

Sample minimums per tier:
- **Zero-shot** (XTTSv2, Tortoise, F5-TTS): 6-30 seconds of clean reference audio.
- **Few-shot** (StyleTTS2 adaptation, XTTSv2 fine-tune): 5-30 minutes paired audio+transcript.
- **Full fine-tune** (VITS from scratch, StyleTTS2 full): 5-50+ hours paired data.

