### Step 2: Verify signature presence

```bash
SIGN_LINE=$(grep -E "^I, .+, on [0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}, consent to the scope above\.$" \
  "$PLAN_ROOT/{voice-slug}/CONSENT.md" || true)
[ -z "$SIGN_LINE" ] && echo "CONSENT_UNSIGNED" || echo "CONSENT_OK"
```

If `CONSENT_UNSIGNED`: stop with "CONSENT.md is not signed. Fill in the signature
line exactly: `I, {name}, on {YYYY-MM-DD}, consent to the scope above.` (no trailing
whitespace). Re-run this skill once signed."

### Step 3: Pick the cloning tier

AskUserQuestion:
- **Simplify:** "There are three tiers of voice cloning. Zero-shot needs almost
  no data but quality has a ceiling. Few-shot is the sweet spot for most production
